11
00:01:57,817 --> 00:01:58,909
Is that short?

12
00:01:59,152 --> 00:02:01,484
Would you marry someone
you'd only known a year?

13
00:02:04,023 --> 00:02:06,321
I can't say I have a lot of hope
for the whole thing.

14
00:02:08,294 --> 00:02:09,784
Then why are we going then?

15
00:02:09,996 --> 00:02:13,432
- We're supporting her.
- I thought she wasn't speaking to you.

16
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,965
No.

17
00:02:15,768 --> 00:02:17,963
I wasn't speaking to her, but I'm over it.

18
00:02:19,906 --> 00:02:21,703
I'm never getting married.

19
00:02:50,403 --> 00:02:52,337
Why aren't you wearing
your new shades?

20
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:54,564
I don't think I need them right now.

21
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:56,706
You begged for those glasses.

22
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:07,719
You look very cool.

23
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:13,315
I don't need them right now.

24
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:21,599
Do they know we're here?

25
00:03:23,469 --> 00:03:24,527
Yes.

26
00:03:40,119 --> 00:03:41,108
Are you...

27
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:45,055
Paul apologizes for not coming.
She's still getting the house ready.

28
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:48,457
I'm sorry it was such short notice.

29
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:51,621
I don't care.
Paul's frantic, but I don't give a shit.

30
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:55,398
And Ingrid wants me to tell you
that she made us all bracelets.

31
00:03:55,501 --> 00:03:56,798
No, I said we should wait.

32
00:03:56,903 --> 00:04:01,636
I thought you asked me to tell them.
Anyway, I got Knicks colors.

33
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:03,174
They're not Knicks colors!

34
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:04,903
It's beautiful, Ingrid.

35
00:04:05,445 --> 00:04:08,039
- Where's your dad and Josh?
- They might come later.

36
00:04:08,147 --> 00:04:11,708
Josh's spring break is next week,
and then Jim teaches through Friday.

37
00:04:11,818 --> 00:04:14,184
Then he opens the house
in Vermont on the weekend.

38
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:16,714
