39
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:18,246
Good.

40
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:22,019
Holy Jesus! Watch it, dicksack!

41
00:04:23,496 --> 00:04:24,485
God!

42
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,901
If you're wondering about
the mustache...

43
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:29,991
No, I wasn't.

44
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:32,537
I had a full beard for a while,
and then when I shaved it

45
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:36,166
I left this part for last, you know,
to see how it looked.

46
00:04:36,743 --> 00:04:37,710
And...

47
00:04:38,544 --> 00:04:39,704
It's meant to be funny.

48
00:04:51,257 --> 00:04:52,849
You're so handsome.

49
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:01,262
I never thought I'd get you here.

50
00:05:07,607 --> 00:05:09,131
You're arriving in the midst of a drama.

51
00:05:09,242 --> 00:05:11,642
Ingrid, would you make sure
Wizard's inside?

52
00:05:11,744 --> 00:05:12,768
It's the Voglers.

53
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:15,143
The neighbours want us
to cut down our tree.

54
00:05:15,248 --> 00:05:17,148
No. That's our tree.

55
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:19,445
They think it's sick
and rotting their property.

56
00:05:19,552 --> 00:05:21,019
We're having the ceremony under it.

57
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,610
You took the swing down.

58
00:05:22,722 --> 00:05:25,953
Pauline thinks this is their way
of trying to be friends.

59
00:05:27,393 --> 00:05:30,760
I think they resent us because we're...

60
00:05:30,863 --> 00:05:32,558
I don't know what we are.

61
00:05:42,408 --> 00:05:44,638
- This is my room.
- Okay.

62
00:05:45,144 --> 00:05:48,204
- Do you like showers or baths?
- Showers. What about you?

63
00:05:48,314 --> 00:05:49,372
I don't care.

64
00:05:49,482 --> 00:05:51,006
Is Malcolm what you thought he'd be?

65
00:05:51,551 --> 00:05:54,111
- I didn't know what to...
- The mustache is temporary.

66
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:55,983
He saved it for last
when he was shaving.

67
00:05:56,089 --> 00:05:57,386
It's meant to be funny.

68
00:05:57,490 --> 00:05:58,718
- He told me.
- Yeah.

69
00:05:59,559 --> 00:06:01,186
I'm sorry, with so little time to prepare,

70
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:03,762
we had to put you in
Malcolm's storage room.

71
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:07,491
This was Becky's room. Poor Becky.

72
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:10,192
Poor Becky.
Well, now it's a storage room.

73
00:06:11,237 --> 00:06:14,468
I've just started to feel like it's
our house and not my parents', you know.

74
00:06:14,574 --> 00:06:15,734
Our parents.

75
00:06:15,842 --> 00:06:17,537
Of course.

76
00:06:17,643 --> 00:06:19,702
Sorry, it might still smell like paint.

77
00:06:19,812 --> 00:06:21,336
I thought he was a musician.

78
00:06:21,447 --> 00:06:24,678
Well, music's officially a hobby.
He's painting now,

79
00:06:24,784 --> 00:06:27,514
and writing letters to newspapers
and magazines.

80
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,046
He's very meticulous.

81
00:06:29,155 --> 00:06:32,124
He'll spend up to a week
writing a response to a music review.

82
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:37,588
He's incredibly smart. Maybe too smart.
I don't know. We're doing very well.

83
00:06:38,331 --> 00:06:41,164
Good. I mean, you must be.

84
00:06:43,202 --> 00:06:45,227
I don't know where to begin.
What can I tell you?

85
00:06:48,341 --> 00:06:51,139
It seems I'm pregnant,
but it's really early,

86
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,712
so I haven't told anyone.
I mean, I haven't told Malcolm or Ingrid.

87
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:55,178
- Wow.
- What did you say?

88
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:56,270
I said wow.

89
00:06:56,382 --> 00:07:00,478
Yeah. If it sticks. We'll see. I hope so.

90
00:07:01,053 --> 00:07:02,213
Things are good.

91
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:05,984
We did a couples' seminar
two months ago or so in Maine.

92
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:07,787
They give you exercises
and things to do.

93
00:07:07,894 --> 00:07:11,352
I know you're not convinced,
but we got engaged right afterwards.

94
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:14,892
The guy who runs it, Strickland,
he wrote this really interesting book,

95
00:07:15,001 --> 00:07:16,969
<i>On Loving,
which I'll lend you if you want.</i>

96
00:07:17,069 --> 00:07:18,036
Okay.

97
00:07:18,137 --> 00:07:19,399
But only if you'll read it.

98
00:07:19,505 --> 00:07:21,564
Because I need it back.
I made notes in the margins.

99
00:07:21,741 --> 00:07:23,436
I may not get to it for a while.

100
00:07:23,543 --> 00:07:26,068
Well, I'm not going to lend it to you
if you're not going to read it.

101
00:07:27,146 --> 00:07:28,704
It's gonna be very informal, by the way.

102
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:31,340
Just Mom and Becky,
Malcolm's brother,

103
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:34,943
a few friends, and now you and Claude.
Nothing like the first one.

104
00:07:35,054 --> 00:07:36,282
Becky's coming?

105
00:07:36,422 --> 00:07:38,151
- Yeah.
- Could I have some...

106
00:07:38,724 --> 00:07:39,625
You go.

107
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:41,817
I was just going to say
could I have some white wine?

108
00:07:41,928 --> 00:07:43,896
Oh, yeah. We have...

109
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:49,527
I'm really glad you changed your mind
and came.

110
00:07:50,102 --> 00:07:53,265
I never heard from you after I sent
the invite. I even wondered if you got it.

111
00:07:53,372 --> 00:07:54,930
I'm just so pleased that we're here.

112
00:07:55,174 --> 00:07:56,141
Did you get it?

113
00:07:56,242 --> 00:07:57,800
Yeah.

114
00:07:57,910 --> 00:07:59,275
I'm sorry you were so angry.

115
00:07:59,378 --> 00:08:01,642
I wasn't angry. I was disappointed.

116
00:08:01,747 --> 00:08:03,578
But you see,
when you say disappointed,

117
00:08:03,683 --> 00:08:05,708
it puts me in a crummy situation,
like I let you down.

118
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:08,116
- Well, you did, in a way.
- No, I don't see it like that.

119
00:08:08,221 --> 00:08:09,779
Fine. I felt betrayed. Is that word okay?

120
00:08:09,889 --> 00:08:11,186
Again, you're making me the aggressor.

121
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:13,349
You were the aggressor.

122
00:08:13,459 --> 00:08:15,086
Listen, let's not...

123
00:08:17,597 --> 00:08:19,394
I've become a really good cook.

124
00:08:24,971 --> 00:08:27,940
I can't believe you've still got
all of our old records.

125
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:31,100
- Mom, can you hide this, please?
- Yeah, of course.

126
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:33,337
Malcolm played with Ric Ocasek once.

127
00:08:33,446 --> 00:08:35,346
Yeah, in the late '80s.

128
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:38,315
After he left The Cars. It was a solo gig.

129
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:39,884
So you're kind of famous?

130
00:08:39,986 --> 00:08:44,514
No, no, believe me, I'm not.
I used to want to be, but no.

131
00:08:44,624 --> 00:08:45,613
Do you want to be famous?

132
00:08:45,725 --> 00:08:47,750
Claude wants to be very famous.

133
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:50,829
Well, make sure you can
handle rejection. I can't.

134
00:08:51,964 --> 00:08:54,660
For me, expectation just
turns to disappointment.

135
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:56,758
So ultimately, I'd rather not try.

136
00:08:57,103 --> 00:08:58,263
Claude, ignore him.

137
00:08:58,671 --> 00:09:01,071
It'll all go black for us
soon enough, anyway.

138
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:03,468
When your mother moved to New York,

139
00:09:03,576 --> 00:09:05,510
she used to send me
books and records.

140
00:09:05,611 --> 00:09:07,704
<i>- She sent me R.E.M.'s Murmur.
- And the Pixies.</i>

141
00:09:07,813 --> 00:09:11,681
And X. She was very cool, your mother.

142
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:15,980
- You only liked Top 40.
- That's true. But I love R.E.M. Now.

143
00:09:17,757 --> 00:09:20,021
I don't really listen to music anymore.

144
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:23,254
I was dating that guy Horace back then.
Do you remember him?

145
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:25,995
Was that the guy
that liked to rough you up?

146
00:09:26,098 --> 00:09:27,895
No, that was our dad.

147
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,265
Our dad used to strip down to
his skiwies and beat us with a belt.

148
00:09:31,370 --> 00:09:33,201
That man had a sexual screw loose.

149
00:09:33,306 --> 00:09:35,433
That's awful that stuff
that happens to kids.

150
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:37,805
Malcolm was fondled
by a male babysitter.

151
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:40,003
Just use that information
however you want.

152
00:09:40,112 --> 00:09:42,580
I'm sorry, we're with family. I figured...

153
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:46,782
I think Becky got it the worst.

154
00:09:46,886 --> 00:09:49,514
Did she ever.
Raped by the horse trainer.

155
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:05,561
Alan rolled over in bed and he looked
at me and he said, "I can't feel my face. "

156
00:10:06,339 --> 00:10:08,933
It took three doctors before
we knew it was Bell's Palsy.

157
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:11,599
They say a brush of wind can do it.

158
00:10:11,711 --> 00:10:13,269
Feeling is slowly coming back.

159
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:16,481
We're all getting older, which is terrible.

160
00:10:16,582 --> 00:10:20,541
I don't care how universal it is.
I can't remember names anymore.

161
00:10:20,653 --> 00:10:24,487
I have that.
I blank out on certain words now, too.

162
00:10:24,590 --> 00:10:27,855
The other day I couldn't remember
the word for...

163
00:10:28,928 --> 00:10:33,262
I've forgotten it again. The stuff in wine.
What is it? Sediment. That's it.

164
00:10:33,366 --> 00:10:34,560
I know that. I was talking more about

165
00:10:34,667 --> 00:10:37,227
not remembering who was
the bassist for Mötley Crüe.

166
00:10:37,370 --> 00:10:40,339
Ingrid. Why don't you show Claude
and Bruce the game trunk?

167
00:10:40,439 --> 00:10:41,406
Okay.

168
00:10:41,507 --> 00:10:42,906
Mick Mars.

169
00:10:51,183 --> 00:10:53,811
Toby, I think you need to have
Bruce diagnosed.

170
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:57,314
Margot, I don't wanna have
this conversation with you.

171
00:10:57,957 --> 00:11:00,949
It's vital. If you keep telling him
he's like everyone else,

172
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:03,893
he's gonna wonder why he isn't.
He's suffering.

173
00:11:03,996 --> 00:11:07,022
He's tested very well.
He does B's in school.

174
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:08,691
But that's how autism works.

175
00:11:08,801 --> 00:11:11,634
One part of the brain can be fine,
and then the other part is damaged.

176
00:11:11,737 --> 00:11:14,865
We've had him diagnosed, Margot.
Nothing was found wrong.

177
00:11:14,974 --> 00:11:16,703
Did you really, though?

178
00:11:17,243 --> 00:11:20,735
I'm not gonna have this conversation.
I'm sorry.

179
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:26,315
I know this must be so difficult for you,
but you have to...

180
00:11:28,254 --> 00:11:29,278
<i>What are you doing?</i>

181
00:11:29,388 --> 00:11:30,980
I left you a note.

182
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:32,216
<i>Come back.</i>

183
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:35,651
<i>Or meet me in Vermont on Saturday.</i>

184
00:11:36,262 --> 00:11:39,925
No. No. The wedding is on Saturday.

185
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:43,058
I'm here for that. I can't pull out.
How would that look?

186
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:46,571
<i>You haven't spoken to her in years.</i>

187
00:11:46,672 --> 00:11:51,371
Well, we're speaking now.
She is my closest friend, despite it all.

188
00:11:51,477 --> 00:11:53,570
You were the one that kept trying
to get me to call her.

189
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:55,476
<i>Did you tell Claude what you're doing?</i>

190
00:11:56,415 --> 00:11:59,441
Jim, this guy, Malcolm,

191
00:12:02,421 --> 00:12:05,413
he's exactly what you'd imagine,
except I think he's clinically depressed.

192
00:12:07,526 --> 00:12:11,462
He's not ugly.
He's just completely unattractive.

193
00:12:11,997 --> 00:12:13,555
He has no job.

194
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:16,760
Best I can make out is
he's a letter writer. I don't know.

195
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:21,032
And the house looks weird to me.
She's trying too hard.

196
00:12:22,007 --> 00:12:23,736
It's all kind of a mess.

197
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:28,569
They took down the swing.

198
00:12:29,548 --> 00:12:30,537
Hello?

199
00:12:30,649 --> 00:12:34,176
<i>You said you weren't 100% on this.
You said that like a week ago.</i>

200
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,487
<i>Can I come up there?</i>

201
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:39,615
No. I don't want to see you.
I feel happier already having done it.

202
00:12:39,892 --> 00:12:43,328
<i>Please, don't tell Claude anything,
please, until we've talked more.</i>

203
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:46,421
This is happening, and you need
to get your mind around that.

204
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:51,227
- Are you asleep?
- Yes.

205
00:12:53,672 --> 00:12:56,300
- Will you remember this?
- Yeah.

206
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:00,739
I just talked to your dad.

207
00:13:02,948 --> 00:13:05,382
I'm only going to tell you
if you won't remember.

208
00:13:07,153 --> 00:13:08,245
Okay.

209
00:13:12,825 --> 00:13:15,919
Everyone finds you so funny
and charming.

210
00:13:16,028 --> 00:13:18,223
I always get compliments about you.

211
00:13:19,965 --> 00:13:23,423
Are you having fun?
Is it nice to see Pauline?

212
00:13:23,536 --> 00:13:27,597
- Yeah, I really like her.
- Yeah, she is crazy, though.

213
00:13:27,706 --> 00:13:30,903
- In what way?
- She's really berserk.

214
00:13:31,443 --> 00:13:33,411
Maybe it's the hormones.

215
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:36,614
You didn't notice anything
different about Pauline?

216
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:40,342
- No.
- She's pregnant. She told me.

217
00:13:40,452 --> 00:13:44,786
She's keeping it a secret
from Malcolm and even Ingrid,

218
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:47,222
which I think is unforgivable.

219
00:13:48,527 --> 00:13:50,757
Now she's gonna have to marry him.

220
00:13:51,297 --> 00:13:52,764
What's she planning on doing,
getting married

221
00:13:52,865 --> 00:13:56,198
and not drinking champagne?
Then she's just gonna be lying.

222
00:13:57,136 --> 00:14:00,037
I guess she's afraid she'll miscarry.
She probably will.

223
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,531
I think on some level,
she's ambivalent about the marriage.

224
00:14:02,641 --> 00:14:04,370
That's why she's not telling him.

225
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:08,040
Are you stoned, Mom?

226
00:14:09,715 --> 00:14:11,307
Maybe a little.

227
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:13,849
I don't like it.

228
00:14:17,890 --> 00:14:20,518
My scrotum is longer than my penis.

229
00:14:24,663 --> 00:14:26,722
It's sweet how Claude looks up to me.

230
00:14:29,501 --> 00:14:32,493
Margot doesn't seem as crazy
as you made her out to be.

231
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:35,802
What she did to Alan and Toby tonight
didn't seem crazy enough for you?

232
00:14:36,675 --> 00:14:38,609
I guess that seemed pretty crazy.

233
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,235
Well, she cares deeply.

234
00:14:40,346 --> 00:14:42,712
Yeah, she's really worried about Bruce.

235
00:14:43,115 --> 00:14:47,211
This has nothing to do with Bruce.
She thinks everyone is autistic.

236
00:14:49,855 --> 00:14:50,844
What?

237
00:14:50,956 --> 00:14:52,480
Nothing.
You keep changing your position.

238
00:14:52,591 --> 00:14:54,718
I'm just trying to figure out
if I should agree with you or not.

239
00:14:54,827 --> 00:14:57,318
Well, can't she be both?
Care deeply and be crazy?

240
00:14:57,429 --> 00:14:59,556
I mean, do people have to be
all one thing?

241
00:14:59,765 --> 00:15:01,960
- I guess not.
- Well, okay then.

242
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:05,962
It is nice she came for the wedding.

